********************************************************************************
*                                                                              *
*                  ===  MERGECOM-3 ADVANCED Messages File ===                  *
*                                                                              *
********************************************************************************
* This file is provided for convenience only.  It list all the messages        *
* supported by the toolkit - and all the attributes in each message.  It       *
* also lists characteristics of each attribute; including VR, VT, defined      *
* terms, enumerated values, conditions, and sequence names for attributes      *
* having a value representation of SQ.                                         *
*                                                                              *
* NOTE:  Value Types (VT's) for attributes of composite services may not agree *
* with the standard when those attributes are contained in conditional modules.*
* The advanced toolkit treats all attributes in conditional modules as type 3. *
* Also, the attributes of N-EVENT Notifications (Responses) in the Normalized  *
* services are all of type 3 - independent of event type.                      *
* If you see any other areas of variation from the DICOM standard, please      *
* report them to Merge eFilm.                                                  *
********************************************************************************
   *                                                                        *
   *                      COPYRIGHT (C) 1994-2002                           *
   *                            Merge eFilm                                 *
   *                     Milwaukee, Wisconsin 53214                         *

   *  This software is furnished under license and may be used and copied   *
   *  only in accordance with the terms of such license and with the        *
   *  inclusion of the above copyright notice.  This software or any other  *
   *  copies thereof may not be provided or otherwise made available to any *
   *  other person.  No title to and ownership of the software is hereby    *
   *  transferred.                                                          *

   **************************************************************************/
